wikipedia_page.main: Dennis Higgins (1915 – 25 September 1942) was an English footballer who played as a forward for Tamworth and Fulham. He was killed in action in World War II.

response: * Dennis Higgins (1915-1942), professional footballer for Tamworth and Fulham before World War II, in which he was killed.

link_mentions.page: List of footballers killed during World War II
response: * Dennis Higgins – played for Fulham. He was killed in action in North Africa on 25 September 1942 aged 26 serving with the Durham Light Infantry.Dennis Higgins
